{
  "guid": "pyfm",
  "name": "Poly FM",
  "description": "This algorithm is inspired by the original Poly FM algorithm on the disting EX. It is a polyphonic, multitimbral, FM synthesizer using the six-operator FM engine from the open-source Plaits module by Ã‰milie Gillet (exactly as used in the Macro Oscillator 2 algorithm). The algorithm loads Yamaha DX7 voice bank SysEx files from the MicroSD card. It supports up to four different timbres, each defined by a distinct voice bank/voice selection and additional parameters shaping sound characteristics. All timbres share a pool of up to 24 simultaneous voices. When adjusting microtuning parameters, more information about the chosen tuning is displayed on the GUI.",
  "categories": [
    "synthesis",
    "polyphonic",
    "FM"
  ],
  "short_description": "A polyphonic FM synthesizer",
  "use_cases": [
    "Generating complex, evolving sounds using Yamaha DX7 voice banks",
    "Creating layered textures with up to four distinct timbres",
    "Responding to MIDI, MPE, or CV/gate inputs for dynamic control"
  ],
  "gui_description": "The display shows the notes being played by the various voices, each superimposed on a bar indicating the note envelope. Additional tuning information appears when microtuning parameters are adjusted.",
